# Enrich OS — environment variables
#
# Deployment hardening (SQLite → Turso/libSQL) is in progress — see
# docs/DEPLOYMENT_HARDENING.md for the authoritative checklist.
#
# Repositories still use the synchronous better-sqlite3 connection in
# server/db/client.ts as of this phase (Phase 1: connection layer
# foundation only). server/db/libsql-client.ts is the new async
# connection, not yet wired into any repository. It reads the two
# variables below, falling back to a local file when unset — so
# `pnpm install && pnpm dev` still works with zero .env config.
#
# All non-persistence configuration lives in version-controlled JSON:
# config/column-aliases.json, config/confidence-weights.json,
# config/descriptor-list.json, config/pipeline-version.json.

# --- Required for local development -----------------------------------
# (none — `pnpm install && pnpm dev` works with no .env file at all;
# server/db/libsql-client.ts defaults to a local file at
# data/enrich-os.db when TURSO_DATABASE_URL is unset)

# --- Required for production (Vercel) -----------------------------------
# TURSO_DATABASE_URL=libsql://<your-db>.turso.io
# TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=<your-turso-auth-token>
#
# Both are required together once the app is deployed — Vercel's
# serverless functions have a read-only filesystem outside /tmp, and
# /tmp does not persist across invocations, so the local-file fallback
# above cannot be used in production.

# --- Supabase-related -----------------------------------------------------
# (none — this project has no Supabase integration and none is planned;
# Turso/libSQL was the approved replacement — see docs/ARCHITECTURE.md)

# --- Optional ---------------------------------------------------------------
# (none)
